}}</ref>

''[[Compute!]]'' called ''Omega Race'' "a real winner for the VIC".<ref name="herman198210">{{cite news | url=https://archive.org/stream/1982-10-compute-magazine/Compute_Issue_029_1982_Oct#page/n133/mode/2up | title=Four New Cartridges for VIC-20 | work=Compute! | date=October 1982 | accessdate=30 October 2013 | author=Herman, Harvey B. | pages=132 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130102074826/https://archive.org/stream/1982-10-compute-magazine/Compute_Issue_029_1982_Oct#page/n133/mode/2up#page/n133/mode/2up | archive-date=2013-01-02 | url-status=live }}</ref> ''[[BYTE]]'' stated that the VIC-20 version "is fast paced, has colorful graphics, and features good sound effects ... ''Omega Race'' is a fun game that retains all the best characteristics of the arcade version".<ref name="wszola198303">{{cite news | url=https://archive.org/stream/byte-magazine-1983-03/1983_03_BYTE_08-03_Mass_Storage#page/n251/mode/2up | title=Omega Race for the VIC-20 | work=BYTE | date=March 1983 | accessdate=19 October 2013 | author=Wszola, Stan | pages=251}}</ref> ''[[Ahoy!]]'' called the VIC-20 version "fairly faithful to the arcade game, and very exciting".<ref name="salm198403">{{cite news | url=https://archive.org/stream/Ahoy_Issue_03_1984-03_Ion_International_US#page/n47/mode/2up | title=VIC Game Buyer's Guide | work=Ahoy! | date=March 1984 | accessdate=27 June 2014 | author=Salm, Walter | pages=49}}</ref> The VIC-20 version of ''Omega Race'' was awarded a Certificate of Merit in the category of "Best Solitaire Computer Game" at the 4th annual [[Arkie Awards]].<ref>{{cite journal |last1= Kunkel |first1= Bill |author-link1= Bill Kunkel (gaming)|last2= Katz |first2= Arnie |author-link2= Arnie Katz|date= March 1983 |title= Arcade Alley: The Best Computer Games |journal= [[Video (magazine)|Video]]|publisher= Reese Communications|volume= 6|issue= 12|pages= 32–33|issn= 0147-8907}}</ref>{{rp|33}}

== Legacy ==
''Omega Race'' was cloned for the [[TRS-80 Color Computer]] as ''Space Race'' in 1982.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Boyle |first1=L. Curtis |title=Space Race |url=http://www.lcurtisboyle.com/nitros9/spacerace.html |website=Tandy Color Computer Games |access-date=2018-06-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180627123847/http://www.lcurtisboyle.com/nitros9/spacerace.html |archive-date=2018-06-27 |url-status=live }}</ref>

An update of the game for the [[Atari Jaguar]] was pitched to [[Atari Corporation]] by Temporary Sanity Designs, however, it never moved forward beyond the proposal phase and the document is in the hands of community member joekorali of [[AtariAge]].<ref>{{cite web|author=joekorali|url=http://atariage.com/forums/topic/141527-atari-jaguar-promo-stuff/page-2#entry1714204|title=Atari Jaguar promo stuff? (Page 2)|website=[[AtariAge]]|date=March 30, 2009|accessdate=2019-01-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite video|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1ijiqurGOa0 |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/varchive/youtube/20211219/1ijiqurGOa0 |archive-date=2021-12-19 |url-status=live|work=[[YouTube]]|date=March 30, 2009|author=successfultroll|title=Atari Jaguar Promo Stuff Part 3 (6min 23sec)}}{{cbignore}}</ref>

